caption: "Turns out, our maze is so hard, even the cheese applied for early retirement."
"I'm afraid the DMV doesn't recognize 'valor and chivalry' as valid forms of insurance."
"As a tailor, Mr. Johnson learned the hard way that some projects simply required a mouse-click escape route."
“This is why I never book the 'Scenic Pyramid View' on Expedia.”
"And there, at the summit, lays the elusive Zenfish—sought by monks and aquarium enthusiasts alike."
"First wish granted: an endless supply of toast. Next?"
"I'm telling you, officer, he thought 'dog park' and 'kite park' were the same thing."
"Darling, I think we've finally discovered where all the water in the apartment is going."
"Sure, they can type — but wait until you see their PowerPoint presentations."
"I don't know, man, the elephant in the room doesn't seem all that metaphorical."
"Do you think he knows it's live?"
"Another detour sign targeted at us, Gary. They just want us to keep off the road!"
"Remember when we used to imagine flying cars? Now we just hope for a working Wi-Fi signal."
"It's a bold piece, but I feel it lacks the emotional range of a well-timed pie to the face."
"Of course I’ll hold... you know the connections here in Siberia are always tangled."
"Does it come with a user manual or do I just wing it?"
"Apparently, the rooftop seating comes with a tangible sense of impending doom."
"Don't worry, the hangover's not the only thing that's going to kill you."
"When you said you wanted the restaurant to feel like home, I didn't realize you meant *our* home."
"Well, it's cheaper than renting surfboards."
"Good try, Moses, but I said TEN commandments, not a top ten list."
"Great gas mileage, zero emissions, and, if you squint, it kind of looks like a Tesla."
"Great, another dinner where you don't let me get a word in edgewise."
"Yes, Larry, that mat has truly seen the glory days of our living room. Now how about we find something a little less… historical?"
"I'll grant you three wishes, but fair warning: every spreadsheet error is on you."
"I'm telling you, Carl, it's an avant-garde performance piece."
"Don't look now, but our lunch has arrived."
"Honestly, Jerry, I blame gentrification."
“Ma’am, we have a strict policy: all emotional support animals must remain outside.”
"Don't worry, he's a vegan — only drinks Bloody Mary's."
"Maybe next time we should invest in a ball of yarn."
"Yes, it's slightly tilted, but on the plus side, it's always ski season."
"License and registration—and, oh yes, your intergalactic passport, please."
"When Susan joined the new group chat, she realized she might need to work on her emoji game."
"It's not the parrot that bothers me—it's the emotional support script."
"Wait, you mean to tell me this isn't Sudoku?"
"Did you really think the Paleo diet was just about what we eat?"
"After the yacht club's lunch, the tip was surprisingly generous."
"The GPS just said 'Turn left in 50 feet for the fun to begin!'"
"Well, Mr. Potato Head, it looks like you're mashed in the head and will need some serious peeling to get to the root of the problem."
"Jerry was always good at thinking outside the (litter) box."
"Get your binoculars — It's the rare and elusive Nesting Bob Dylan Bird."
"His work-from-home attire is a balance between cabin fever and staying 'current' on events."
"I swear, if that’s another Earth infomercial package, I am canceling our cable!"
"And the award for 'Worst Scheduling Error' goes to..."
"Sir Lancelot, I hereby decree that from this day forth, we shall be known as the Knights Who Say... 'Ouch'"
"Why yes, Sir Nigel, this is the most noble spot to avoid the in-laws."
"While the merger was unorthodox, integrating the Viking division and the accounting team proved surprisingly effective."
"And just like that, our family vacation turned into a corporate takeover."
"Okay, but if you're here, who's in the conference call?"
"I'm telling you, Doc, every time I close my eyes, I see butter."
"Of course we're from another planet. This is the only place in the universe where you can get free leaves."
"And this is why we don't have a basement."
"Dry cleaners closed, so I thought I'd air dry."
"Do the pills come in carrot flavor?"
"Yes, Jerry, I see you’ve brought the proverbial elephant in the room to therapy."
"Well, Mr. Stickman, your resume looks a bit thin, but I hear you're great under pressure."
"Hey Carol, see anything about a heated dome on Airbnb?"
"Do you accept payment in hibernation naps or just Salmon Pay?"
"Well, it looks like your chart is lit… literally."
"Yes, Mr. Wiggins, we *all* read Hemingway in college."
"He's upset because Max just got promoted to 'First Born'."
"You may laugh now, but just wait until he's hosting Late Night at the age of 10."
"Okay, Google, order 3,000 pacifiers and a one-way ticket to Grandma's."
"I decided to branch out into the corporate world, but now I’m just pining for my old forest job."
"I asked for the soup of the day, but I didn't expect today's special to be a tornado."
"Welcome to the new 'Stress Management' elevator, where you float through your problems on the way to the top."
"The critics warned him his performance would be a knockout—guess he took it literally."
"Sir, I’d recommend changing the spark plugs and reconsidering your entire career path."
"It's never too early to start preparing them for student loans."
"Jerry, I told you we were getting two separate cones. This is not what I meant by a 'team-building exercise.'"
"That's Steve from accounting. He’s been outsourcing his tasks to quicksand."
"Well, Charles, if you'd just asked for directions, we wouldn't be in this mess!"
"Look Steve, if you're going to insist on 'armoring up' for performance reviews, we're going to need a bigger office."
"I'm not sure, Greg. Does this make me look like I'm only here for the 401(k)?"
"Later, when asked about Napoleon's first horse, the historian added, 'Technically, it cost 50 cents and was located next to the grocery store.'"
"Sure, it's the apocalypse, but at least Gabriel finally found a use for his blindfold."
"He swore there was Wi-Fi at the summit."
"Sure, Dr. Hale, but when you said a deep, immersive therapy session, I didn't think you meant it literally."
"Stanley, this isn't a stage. Stop raking like you're in a Broadway musical and just get the yard cleaned up."
"Sure, Karen, you can have the last breadstick."
"Turns out, the Dyson 8000 is also great at finding your lost dignity."
"Maybe we should talk about why 'Take Your Pet to Work Day' isn't catching on, Bob."
"Well, I guess this means the promotion isn't happening."
"In the age of social media, even rabbits have Instagram accounts."
"Steve, we really need to stop thinking outside the box for our summer vacation plans."
"I don’t fear commitment, doctor. I just have severe clock-a-phobia."
"We signed him for his invisibility, but it turns out the guy's just really good at hiding."
"Listen, Frank, I'm not saying it isn't efficient, I'm just saying it might be a bit much for a quick run to the grocery store."
"Welcome to the quarterly board meeting. Remember, no sliding into conclusions without everyone's input."
"Steve regretted suggesting the tandem bike long before they hit the hill."
"Honestly, Brenda, ever since you started reading historical fiction, it's been nothing but surprise visits."
"Honestly, Larry, if you forgot our anniversary again... who’s the real zombie here?"
"Well, we can't all rely on seasonal work, Janet."
"In my professional opinion, your procrastination seems to be hitting new heights."
"Well Gary, you did say you wanted a room with a better view of the night sky."
"Johnson, you were in charge of ordering the new conference table, weren't you?"
"Well, Gerald, if you wanted to discuss the peanut in the room, you could’ve just asked."
"Look, Gabriel, I don't care how you do it—just make sure Earth pockets last."
"Frank promptly regretted asking Timmy for a 'shovel of encouragement.'"
"Now this one comes with complimentary squirrels and a premium leaf view."
"If he asks for your Wi-Fi password, just lie and say it's complicated."
"And that, Dr. Johnson, is the third rat this month to complete the maze in under 10 seconds. I think we're going to need a tougher maze."
"I'm telling you, Martha, this new workout regime really elevates your senses."
"Honestly, Rapunzel, I thought about a ladder, but this felt more personal."
"Of course he's in charge of the self-help section. He's the most disarming one here."
"Next time, we'll take separate cars. I told you whale-watching wasn't a spectator sport."
"And that, everyone, is how Bob from HR suggests we tackle interdepartmental communication."
"Welcome to Hell. Please enjoy our uninterrupted 24/7 news coverage."
"Well, there goes the neighborhood watch committee’s newest ‘stay alert' initiative."
"Listen, Carl, if you want to blend in around here, you need a bit more zig and a lot more zag."
"Relax, Mr. Johnson. This is just how we review patient feedback."
"Well, I guess we'll have to reclassify Earth as the planet of the soggy tennis balls."
"We really need to talk to the shepherd about boundaries."
"Of course I’m sitting down. This is what happens when we binge-watch ‘Planet Earth.'"
"I'm really sorry, but our dress code does state 'no swimwear'."
"Turns out, a bigger Wi-Fi halo doesn't improve the heavenly connection."
"Next stop: International Talk Like a Pirate Day headquarters."
"I've reviewed your life, and I must say, those pants alone have earned you a second chance."
"We really need to stop outsourcing our poles to Escher Enterprises."
"I call this piece 'Abstract Mammoth.' The challenge was capturing your essence without getting trampled."
"It's elementary, Watson. The answer to 42 across is clearly 'banal.'"
"Inkblot, you really need to stop projecting."
"I'm telling you, Susan, this is how you assert dominance in an HOA meeting."
"You have the right to remain silent, but I recommend you tell him how you made the giraffe."
"Alright everyone, let's try to get through the agenda before the new CEO needs watering."
"Yes, the rent is steep, but you'll never have to hear 'Laundry Day' as an excuse again."
"Honestly, I’d take the train noise over the neighbors’ conspiracy theories any day."
"Well, the brochure never mentioned the seasonal dry spell."
"I mean, sure, Greg, but is pushing a boulder really a 'growth industry'?"
"So, are you drafting or jousting?"
"Remember, Sheila, it’s just like that team-building trust fall exercise — but with more quicksand and fewer HR forms."
"Frank's hybrid approach to combining work and leisure hit a snag when he realized his laptop wasn't waterproof."
"Sure, Jack, you grew the beanstalk, but your cloud-presentation game is seriously lacking."
"Okay, step one: Evict the humans."
"Actually, it's pronounced 'Lou-FISH-ee'."
"While I admire your commitment to multitasking, Jim, maybe let's switch 'Dinner Mode' off Carpool Karaoke?"
"I'm sorry, but do you have an appointment? We’re booked solid until 2073."
"Next time, I'm ordering from the 'Dinner for Two' menu instead."
"I don't care what your legal strategy is, Gerald. Tell your clients to stop using the term 'mutton.' "
"Fine, I'll admit it — death metal wasn't exactly what I had in mind for 'easy listening'."
"I warned you, Steve. If we're breaking out the Merlot, I won't be the only one coughing up furballs tomorrow."
“At first I thought he was quirky, but turns out he's just a regular at inflatable tube man conventions.”
"So, are they here for the pizza or to critique your choice of wine?"
"Great, Baxter. You've scared away *another* Hulk."
"Yeah, it's a good read, but the ending really drags."
"You know you're in trouble when even Poseidon forgot the sunscreen."
"Technically, he's still falling."
"Look, Carl, if you're going to start complaining about 'palm trees,' we have bigger issues to discuss."
"And for your last mistake, you failed to list 'escape artist' on your résumé."
"I appreciate the flair, Mr. Pennypacker, but we're here to discuss your parking tickets, not your latest magic trick."
"Excuse me, miss—would you mind sharing that tray? I have six bags of pretzels."
"Well, Steve, if it means we don’t have to go visit your parents, you can transform into whatever you like."
"Yes, it's true. Our therapist said we needed more space, but we thought this was a good start."
"Honey, the shirt press is one thing, but who asked you to iron out the kinks in our marriage?"
"The band's sound really evolved once they added Fish to the lineup."
"Honestly, Rapunzel, there's got to be an easier way to get an appointment at your salon."
"My dear, it’s clear her social distancing measures are more advanced than ours."
"I said I wanted a date that was smooth, not a smoothie!"
"Not now, Janet. Let’s just take the stairs."
"Is that new, or are you just circling the same old ideas?"
"Through the power of hypnosis, Whiskers ensured that the 3 a.m. fridge raids were for tuna only."
"Knock 3 times and Elon Musk delivers your groceries."
"You're in great shape for your age. Looks like you've been reserving yourself nicely."
"Brace yourselves, lads — it’s gonna be a grater battle than we’ve ever faced."
"Your Highness, it’s just a cold — no need to abdicate the throne yet."
"Of course, Dr. Cheese. But do remember, 'lab rat' is just a figure of speech."
"And how does it feel to not always be in the driver's seat?"
"If there's no Wi-Fi at the peak, we've carried this house for nothing."
"Don't worry, that's just Carl from accounting. He's really bad at picking conference rooms."
"Well, at least the commute isn't boring anymore."
"I understand you want to go up, but this is just the elevator to the penthouse, not the space station."
"Is this where I pick up my order of enlightenment to-go?"
"Ahab, aisle five: whaling supplies."
"Sorry, Ricardo. Before I can save this shot, we need to address my fear of commitment."
"Bob was really taking this 'back to the sandbox' team-building exercise literally."
"Honestly, I miss the days when a clubbing involved actual clubs."
"Well, I found enlightenment, but I’m still struggling with Brahms."
"Phil, I think we overdid the 'social distancing' thing."
"She plays the bass, he shovels the treble."
"You came all this way for enlightenment? I'm just here for the chair yoga."
"You know, Bill, when you said you got a pet that doubles as a conversation starter, this isn't what I pictured."
"When Sheila said she needed more emotional support while climbing, this isn't what she had in mind."
"Turns out, the island didn't come with unlimited beach access."
"It's not that we didn't appreciate the housewarming gift, Frank — it's just that our prehistoric HOA has a strict 'no working drawbridge' policy."
"And that's when I decided to cut out the middleman and sell direct to the bull."
"I'm sorry, Chef Gordon, but I had to call. The soufflé fell and confessed everything."
"Ladies and gentlemen, in case of emergency, your tray table will magically transform into a flotation device."
"Of course, sir — and how would you like your canaries served today?"
"Listen, Noah, we need to address the plumbing issues before the flood actually starts."
"I told you we should have invited Karen. Now the sky's angry."
"We're just as surprised as you that our NFT turned into an actual frame."
“All right, we’ve got Happy, Grumpy, Sleepy, Bashful, and now… Roller Derby.”
“Sure, Carl, but could we discuss your tunnel vision next session?”
"Ever since the humans got here, nothing's been the same. First it was the Instagrammers, now it's pineapple on our lily pads."
"So, as you can see from the charts, your son is not only gifted but also quite magical."
"Yes, dear, I know it’s a mammoth task, but it’s my night to cook."
"Well, Sandra, on the bright side, we certainly won't need a bug zapper."
"Sorry, buddy, but the 'No Pets' policy includes emotional support clowns."
"Honestly, Janice, it's not our fault you're the only one without noise-canceling instincts."
"I ordered a sous-chef, not a knight in shining armor."
"Yes, Henry, I agree the stock market crash is troubling, but I feel there’s another issue we need to address."
"I told you we should have gone with the harp."
"Don't worry, these cheese supplements are perfectly safe and FDA-approved."
"Surprisingly, it’s the cheese sculptures they find the most derivative."
"Frank, this isn't what I meant when I said we should 'pop' into nature for some fresh air."
"Yes, Mr. Armstrong, the moonwalk needs a moon-tailored suit."
"I told you, Jerry. When they say, 'Think outside the box,' they don't mean our quarterly reports."
"Wait, you mean you didn’t RSVP either?"
"Look, just because we’re apex predators doesn’t mean we can’t enjoy a little surf-and-turf."
"I told you Marie, we need a much bigger fireplace if you insist on going full festive."
"Some said the desert made you crazy; others just couldn't resist a parade of one."
"Mr. Schwartz was the only one who read the memo about the mandatory company nap meetings."
"Well, Dave, if this is your idea of a mid-life 'prick' crisis, it's working."
“So, Mr. Baxter, tell me about the first time you felt invisible.”
"Looks like another one misunderstood the 'high altitude' tour package."
"No, sir, we haven't accepted doubloons since last Tuesday."
"As you can see, the hero's journey narrative structure is quite universal."
"Well, not so much Moonrise Kingdom as Moonshine Kingdom."
"Sure, Greg, but we all know who the true master of 'bat out of hell' is."
"Dining in the train station is all about atmosphere. Tonight's special is called 'Missed Connections.'"
"Hang in there, Carl. Winter is coming, but at least we don't have to shovel."
"He insists on sleeping in the cave, but insists on the indoor-outdoor slippers."
"Turns out, in this case, the chicken was just in the witness protection program."
"I'm not saying it has to be a dirty martini, but can you make it brackish at least?"
"Look, after this joust, can we discuss how I'm getting zero credit for dragon slaying on LinkedIn?"
"Sorry, sir, but dressing in black tie alone doesn't make you 'rye' bread."
"Well, Gary, looks like we hooked ourselves some real ‘light bites’ today."
"I'm telling you, Frank, cryogenically frozen escargot is the next big thing."
"First date jitters? Just keep telling yourself, 'He's more interested in elk.'"
"Scalpel, please. And cue 'Stayin' Alive.'"
"Any requests for the next chapter? No? How about a refill?"
"We ruled out measles, chickenpox, and shingles, so now all that's left is gingerbread dermatitis."
"Now, if you'll excuse us, we're late for our book club."
"Ever since the slip, I've had serious trust issues."
"As it turns out, Frosty didn’t take no for an answer."
“Doctor, this is just how my anxiety feels.”
"We should have known ET would take his vacation homes seriously."
"Just ignore him, he's been on an 'outside the box' kick since that executive retreat."
"Welcome to 'Art & Appetizers', where the only thing more abstract than the paintings is the concept of grilling indoors."
"I'm telling you, sergeant, this is why we don't let Darwin work late shifts."
"Henry started wearing the toupee after the incident with the wind farm."
“Take me to your veader.”
"Honestly, Fred, every time you forget to preheat the cave, breakfast is just unbearable."
"Of all the critics, we had to get the one who always brings snacks."
"Welcome to Earth. Now, do you take debit or credit?"
"I'm not sure a side of baked beans will help us decide on the cherry or walnut finish."
"And that, Harold, is why I told you not to give the cat your laptop password."
"Your Highness, in conclusion, the proposed budget cuts should alleviate your fiscal anxieties... though I suggest adding 'Sword Removal Technician' to the payroll."
"I swear, Sheila, you ask one marine biologist for directions and suddenly it’s ‘Are you seeing other crustaceans?’"
"Living in Arizona, you have to learn to dodge all the prickly personalities."
"I’m not sure this is what they meant by 'expanding your social bubble.'"
"It was clear — none of the pharaohs anticipated the Great Sphinx's midday snack time."
"Alright team, let's squash this Q4 slump before things get seedy."
"I'd like to introduce you to Mr. Jenkins. He'll be micro-managing you from now on."
"Great, Thunk. Now invent the elevator."
"Looks like we’re finally addressing the elephant-trout in the room."
"I told you we should have brought the maple syrup, Karen."
"No rush. I've almost made it to the entrees."
"It's called 'Uber-Leg,' and it's revolutionizing my morning commute."
"Relax, Sir Lancelot, we'll resume the kidnapping right after the tiebreaker."
"Ever since we subscribed to that wildlife channel, things have really gotten out of hand."
"Trust me, the wolf in sheep’s clothing was so last season. Have you considered the zebra?"
"Looks like someone didn't get the memo about Casual Friday."
"William, seriously, it's just a hat with a cherry on top."
"Well, at least one of us is having a great night under the full moon."
"Ever since we ran out of treats, his shadow’s been on strike."
"I’m telling you, Dave — until we start paying tribute in tuna, there will be no peace talks."
"I think we've taken the ‘working from home’ experiment a bit too far."
"In retrospect, the Viking theme was a bold choice."
"And when did you first realize Mr. Snuggles couldn't be trusted as an alibi?"
"Good news, your assets are in great shape, but your liquidity could use some exercise."
"Doc, I just can't seem to chill."
"Trust me, Adam, this pie is way more interesting than any apple."
"Yes, Harold, it's cool. But have you considered the asteroid?"
“Given that you feel unappreciated, let's start with how the couch makes you feel.”
“Well, maybe it’s time to get GPS for our conversations too.”
"Despite the delays, Norman couldn't help but appreciate the airline's commitment to authenticity."
"Look, we all have our coping mechanisms, Peter."
"If we announce the Wi-Fi password, they might never leave."
"Well, Karen, on the bright side, it looks like we're getting that open office plan you always wanted."
"Look, Carl, if you're going to call them 'horseshoes,' I'm going to take it literally."
"Behold, the Great Houdini’s final trick: corporate downsizing!"
"I knew the promotion would go to his head, but this is ridiculous."
"In retrospect, subscribing to the 'All-You-Can-Eat Streaming Service' was a mistake."
"I said we should strike out more, not move into the bowling alley!"
“Oh great, first it was the bees, now they're sending kids to pollinate.”
"Ugh, ever since they got indoor Wi-Fi, they've totally forgotten about us."
"Harold's new security system was a bit overkill, but no one dared to double dip in the guacamole again."
"Just hexed my ex. Three likes already!"
"For the last time, Carl, it's a peace offering, not a pancake offering."
"Frank, I know the third quarter meteor is concerning, but let's focus on diversifying our asteroid portfolio."
"And in conclusion, let me reiterate: it's not a popularity contest, it's a planetarity contest."
“Looks like the espresso bandits struck again, partner.”
"Next time, let’s just pretend we didn’t find the treasure."
"Sure, I've got my problems. But hey, at least I don't have your dry cleaning bill."
"I can handle the leaves, but I draw the line at intergalactic toddlers."
"Look, I know we got off on the wrong foot with the whole 'kidnapping the princess' thing, but can we just chalk it up to a bad first date?"
"Actually, Karen, I've decided to outsource our HR to someone who can really give a hoot."
"Y'know, Jake, some days I feel like I'm saddled with nothing but treble."
"Honestly, Harold, you could have just told me you didn’t like my cooking."
"Somehow, I think our SOS in E minor might be sending mixed signals."
"Finally, Karen understood why the world looked so flat to everyone else."
"Did you say gluten-free or glue trap free?"
"Well, that explains why your yoga routine was feeling a bit constricting lately."
"This diet plan has just one rule: only eat if you absolutely, positively can't stand it anymore."
"Don't look now, but I think we just lost our tour guide to a crypto board meeting."
"They must have a meeting in the south."
"Yes, Kevin, I get it. You prefer reading e-books now."
"Despite their differences, the Monday morning rush hour clique was a well-oiled machine with only one objective: ignore the guy stuck in the sidewalk crack."
"And then, at the stroke of midnight, the humans invented fire insurance!"
"The flurry in a hurry to prove who's the heavyweight chump."
"Relax, it's just king casual Friday."
"So you're saying you're not 'emotionally unavailable,' but more 'structurally unsound?'"
"You wanted a raise, right?"
"Guys, I told you ‘Rock’ isn’t a genre, it’s a prophecy."
"Unfazed, Throg thought to himself, 'Base-ball no different than mammoth ball, except smaller target and less chance of being trampled.'"
"Autumn had a smile on everything except their dwindling pumpkin spice lattes."
"According to your résumé, you're a natural at slow and steady. The question is, can you handle fast and absurd?"
"I'm telling you, Detective, the suspect is a master of nesting deception."
“Apparently, they take casual Fridays very seriously here.”
"Look, I know you're Death, but you can't just 'take' my queen!"
“Look, I don’t make the rules, but rock, paper, and scissors can only be served together on Tuesdays.”
"When budget cuts hit the Wild West, the high-speed chases took a hit too."
"And this is where I keep my trophies from the annual Fantasy Football league."
“Next time, let's just take the bread-making workshop.”
"You see, Harold, this is why we can't ignore the elephant in the room."
"Jerry, I told you to network, not to bring Death himself to lunch!"
"I know it's midnight, Harold, but it's National Clean Your House Day somewhere."
"It's surreal. We live our whole lives avoiding them, and now they're in a museum."
"Remember, keep your visor down during board meetings. It’s our only defense against those PowerPoint presentations."
"Note to self: Next time, just say we’re out of change."
"If you ask me, Gary’s mid-life crisis is getting a bit out of hand."
"Have you tried... not barking up the wrong tree?"
“I don't care if we saved a lot on airfare, Jim—I'm not putting on lotion for a staycation.”
"Another busy day in Brooklyn: Tax advice, tarot readings, and apparently, house calls in pajamas."
"Behold, the mighty Pipe Organ—a triumph of music and heating efficiency!"
"You know, sometimes it feels like the whole company's emotional baggage is in this briefcase."
"Johnson, for the fifth time this quarter, we need brighter ideas, not slider pitches."
"30 minutes or the pizza's free, and yes, that includes the scaffolding."
"Yes, Susan, it's organic. But let’s not get hung up on the farm-to-table thing."
“Of course it's gluten-free — I threw it above 10,000 feet!”
"Introducing the new Royal Hammock — for those days when ruling feels like a bit too much."
"Well, the good news is, he doesn't mind house calls."
"Jerry regretted combining his Monday morning call with Cowboy Yoga."
"She figured out that as long as she travels as ‘carry-on,’ she flies for free."
"Yes, I'm gluten-free, but I'm also steak-curious."
"We've mastered intergalactic travel, but we still can’t find the food court."
"And just when I was about to break par, they showed up asking for their ball back."
"Honestly, your honor, we argue that 'Reaper on the beach' is purely artistic expression."
"Well, it ain't the Kentucky Derby, but he's sure makin' a run for the Olympic team."
"The shore thing is to relax and whale away the afternoon.”
"Just trying to raise the steaks during rush hour."
"Yes, dear, it’s a great idea to float. But I'm just here for a midnight snack."
"Susan, I'll be working from home indefinitely — HR says I need to remove my backstabber."
"I have to admit, Lance, your 'guard up' approach to dating is really starting to weigh on me."
"We should really talk to our travel agents."
"Corporate announced a cloning initiative to increase productivity. Now, let's try to sort out who's who."
"Well, technically, I am a 'lifeguard' for the kingdom."
"Well, I would have just pinned it to the fridge, but I guess wearing the grocery list works too."
"Gary, we specifically said 'cliff notes,' not 'cliff climbing.'"
"Jim had finally reached his cardio zenith: the hamster wheel at the home office."
"I told you we should have taken that left turn at the imaginary intersection."
"I think the directions said to preheat the grill to 'Manual Mode'."
"Ah yes, the ‘Ex-Rib-Eater’ special. Bon appétit, madame."
"I told you that couples yoga class was a bad idea."
"Looks like we found opposite ends of the 'work from home' spectrum."
"Do you ever wonder if out there, there's a dog staring back at us, pondering the meaning of bones?"
"I understand, Dave, but I'm afraid 'banjo antics' isn't commonly listed under 'midlife crisis'."
"Well, Martha, it’s either Route A or wait for the express wildebeest migration."
"And that's when I decided it was easier to bring the flock to Manhattan than counting them every night."
"Audrey finally understood why Barry had insisted on calling it 'home base.'"
"Frank, it's not that I don't appreciate the effort, but these candlelit dinners take forever."
"Nature's peace and quiet seemed to have its own plans this year."
"I told you downsizing would be ruff, but this is just absurd."
"Frankly, Steve, if you want me to think outside the box, you have to respect my morning process."
"Pssst, buddy. Looking to adopt? These fell off the back of a truck."
"Luckily for you, Jake here starting fetching five years earlier."
